				<li id="16657865" class="cmnt-root" data="-13" data-d="1651268830000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><a class="comment-username" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&u=151312" rel="nofollow"  target="_blank" style="color: #;">JanusAg</a></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578171/Scholar's-Shield" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">29 Apr 2022 17:47</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16657865" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">PROS: Lasts much longer (60 sec) than other shield buffs (Immutable Shield = 30s; Barricade Shield = 5s). Increases guard boost by 25% = Less stamina damage on block. Low INT requirement (12) makes it very accessible to non-INT mains. CONS: Buff is removed if you sheathe your shield (i.e. switch weapons or 2h other weapon) use Barricade Shield (overwrites this &amp; vice versa). The first one is a big issue since you can&apos;t use your main hand weapon art without losing this buff. Alternatively you could put &quot;No Skill&quot; on your shield, but IMO I&apos;d take Parry/Carian Retaliation/Barricade Shield over this. It&apos;s not cheap FP-wise either, so losing the buff hurts. Given the sacrifices needed to use this, I personally found it not worth using in most situations.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16657865" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-166